name: Origami iPhone Slipcase - London Tan
description:
iPhone card holder slipcase cut using the natural spring of the hide to hold your phone securely, then willingly relinquishing it's grip when gently squeezed. Card slot on the front and open pocket on the reverse for larger items such as tickets and receipts. 

Made from butter smooth and gloriously supple English Bridle Shoulder, a leather that is tanned in the traditional fashion using natural vegetable tannins. This process is entirely organic and takes a month to complete, resulting in a leather that feels beautiful and ages just the way you always want, but so rarely get. 

Available in sizes to fit iPhone 5s 5c 5 and 4 models, in Pitch Black, London Tan and Bonfire Red

name: Origami Billfold Wallet
description:
Classic style billfold wallet, executed in a unique way with a one piece folded construction enabling it to easily swallow £500 in £20 pound notes and enough cards to get you into trouble.

Easily holds large quantities of the highest denomination of most major international currencies.

Folded size - 9.5cm x 9.5cm

Available in London Tan, Pitch Black or Bonfire Red.

Made from butter smooth and gloriously supple English Bridle Shoulder, a leather that is tanned in the traditional fashion using natural vegetable tannins. This process takes a month to complete, resulting in a leather that feels beautiful and ages just the way you always want, but so rarely get.

name: Key Compact
description:
Everybody has keys to keep safe, and precious possessions to keep well away from those serrated terrors as they rattle around in your bag or overcoat pocket, scratching, tearing and entangling themselves in a troublesome fashion.

A smiling, folding keyring that could hold the keys to your house, boat, bike, helicopter, shed, guitar case, wine cellar, observatory, vestry, gas meter or loved ones heart. 

Available in London Tan, Pitch Black and Bonfire Red

name: Origami Card Wallet
description:
The matching card holder to the Origami Wallet, with adjusted proportions to let it safely carry plenty of plastic. Up to 16 cards, or 8 cards and a handfull of folded currency, receipts, tickets and that photo of you doing a kickflip under the Eiffel tower in 1996.

Folded size - 7.5cm x 9.5cm

Available in London Tan, Pitch Black and Bonfire Red.

name: Undercover Moleskine Cover - Large
description:

No more dogeared cardboard covers, this will keep things tidy until your ink runs dry. 

Comes complete with 1 Moleskine 13 x 21cm Journal with 80 pages of plain paper.

name: Military Escape Map Cushion
description:
Cold War era military issue escape map, carefully cut and constructed into a cushion. Backed with black heavy weight wool with black piping.

Each cushion is slightly different, depending on which area of the map it is cut from. All will have an area of land and coastline in addition to some glorious 1950's technical typography.

Takes a standard issue cushion pad 18" (45cm) square.
